essentially it's not the most ideal
solution.

227
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:09,000
Now, we've had smart pools on Ergo as
well.

228
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:14,000
These were a good idea, I think, but they
didn't fully decentralize the entire

229
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:19,000
process of mining.

230
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:23,000
There was also another smart pool
initiative on Ethereum while it was proof

231
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:27,000
of work.

232
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:31,000
It was also quite decentralized, however,
it lacked efficiency.

233
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:34,000
And that's something that is really
